detailedReviews.author: Angelo Guzman
detailedReviews.text:
Terrible Service ‚Äì Never Even Got to Try the Pizza

I decided to order delivery from Times Square Pizza for the first time, but unfortunately, I never got to try the food because of their terrible service. When I placed my order, I was told it would arrive in 40 minutes. Over an hour later (an hour and 10 minutes to be exact), I called to check on the status. The person on the phone assured me the pizza would be there ‚Äúany moment.‚Äù

When I asked if the driver had change for a $100 bill, they told me they don‚Äôt accept $100 bills at all. This was never mentioned during the order process. I asked what we should do, and instead of offering a solution, the lady casually suggested voiding the order. By then, my two kids had been waiting over an hour for dinner.

To make matters worse, I found out the food hadn‚Äôt even left the pizzeria. Despite being told the driver was ‚Äúon the way,‚Äù the pizza was still sitting at the restaurant. And when I asked how long it would take to get the food, they said it would be another 40 minutes!

The pizza might be great, but I‚Äôll never know because I couldn‚Äôt get past the awful service. How does a pizzeria not have change for a $100 bill or fail to communicate honestly with their customers? Waiting nearly two hours with two hungry kids only to be told the food hasn‚Äôt left yet is unacceptable. I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place to anyone based on their lack of professionalism and poor customer service.

detailedReviews.author: Nicole Bennett
detailedReviews.text: My family is from NY and moved here in 2004. For the past 20 years we have tried, desperately, to find a pizza place that could come, at least, close to NY pizza. After a few years we just started eating Hungry Howies, Pizza Hut, etc., not because we particularly cared for it but because if we were going to eat subpar pizza, we might as well save a buck. Finally, we tried Times Square Pizza and found that it was close to what we were loved in NY. The crust is crisp but not burnt, the sauce has a nicely seasoned taste but not that ‚Äúout of the can‚Äù taste and the cheese is generously spread on but not too cheesy where it takes over the pizza. They also make zeppoles, which besides that they are shaped different, taste just like home! They have coupons, if you sign up with text, every week and they even run a raffle. The only reason I didn‚Äôt give them 5 stars on atmosphere is because their chairs could stand to be replaced. My husband, and I used to stop in and dine there for lunch on the weekends but I have a bad back and I can‚Äôt sit in the chairs for a whole lunch. Otherwise, the phone is answered quickly and politely, the pickup time is rather quick and the end product is amazing! I highly recommend Times Square Pizza and this is coming from a NYer!
